# Scoreboard Template

**Use:** Every monthly episode opens with the scoreboard. Same format every time. Don't editorialize on the numbers in the graphic itself — let them speak.

The internal version (kept private, not on YouTube) has additional fields. The public version is below.

---

## Public scoreboard (YouTube + blog)

```
MONTH {{n}} — {{month}} {{year}}

REVENUE
  Revenue this month:     ${{revenue_this_month}}
  MRR end of month:       ${{mrr_end_of_month}}
  Active clients:         {{active_clients}}
  Cumulative revenue:     ${{cumulative_revenue}}

ACTIVITY
  Cold emails sent:       {{emails_sent}}
  Replies received:       {{replies}} ({{reply_rate}}%)
  Positive replies:       {{positive_replies}} ({{positive_rate}}%)
  Discovery calls held:   {{calls_held}}
  Proposals sent:         {{proposals_sent}}
  Deals closed:           {{deals_closed}}

EFFORT
  Hours worked:           {{hours_worked}}
  Effective hourly:       ${{effective_hourly}}

vs LAST MONTH
  Said I'd:
    → {{goal_1}}: {{goal_1_result}}
    → {{goal_2}}: {{goal_2_result}}
    → {{goal_3}}: {{goal_3_result}}

GOALS FOR NEXT MONTH
  → {{next_goal_1}}
  → {{next_goal_2}}
  → {{next_goal_3}}
```

## Visual treatment

**Static graphic** — not animated, not flashy. Display for 60 seconds during the scoreboard segment. Voiceover reads it.

**Font:** Same monospace font as your dev environment (consistent visual identity).

**Color palette:**
- Background: matte black `#0a0a0a`
- Text: off-white `#e8e8e8`
- Norse accent: deep gold `#c9a64a` (used sparingly — just for the section headers or month label)
- Red callout: `#c43838` (only used when a number is bad — keeps it impactful)
- Green callout: `#3a8a3a` (only used when a number beats target)

Red/green should appear sparingly. If every number is highlighted, the highlighting means nothing.

